3. Product Vision & Principles

3.1 Vision Statement
"Every person should be able to describe their dream home and watch it come to life, with AI handling the complexity of design, coordination, and construction management from the first sketch to the final walkthrough."

3.2 Core Design Principles

	•	Vibe-First Design: Users describe feelings, aesthetics, and lifestyle needs. The AI translates vibes into specifications. Users should never need to think in architectural terms unless they want to.
	•	AI as Project Manager: The AI is not a passive tool. It is the active project manager that monitors, decides, escalates, and reports. It operates autonomously within defined guardrails and defers to the user only when human judgment is required.
	•	Trello as the Living Contract: The Trello board is the single source of truth. Every stakeholder interacts with it. Every AI action is reflected on it. Every change is tracked through it.
	•	Transparency by Default: Every AI decision, vendor communication, cost estimate, and schedule change is logged, auditable, and visible to the homeowner in real time.
	•	Speed Without Sacrifice: The backend must be blazingly fast. Design generation in under 60 seconds. Vendor matching in under 30 seconds. Board updates in under 5 seconds. Daily reports generated and delivered before 7:00 AM local time.
	•	Dispute Prevention Over Resolution: The system proactively identifies potential conflicts and surfaces them before they escalate. When disputes do occur, structured workflows resolve them quickly with full documentation.

4. User Personas

4.1 Primary Persona: The Homeowner ("The Dreamer")
A first-time or experienced homeowner who wants to build a custom home but lacks the expertise, time, or patience to manage the traditional construction process. They can describe what they want but cannot translate that into blueprints, permits, or contractor schedules.

Attribute
Details
Age Range
30-55
Tech Comfort
Moderate to high; uses apps daily, comfortable with Trello-style tools
Budget Range
$250K - $2M+ build cost
Pain Points
Overwhelmed by complexity, fears going over budget, cannot evaluate contractor quality
Key Need
A single platform that handles everything from design to move-in
Interaction Mode
Natural language prompts, Trello board review, mobile notifications

4.2 Secondary Persona: The General Contractor ("The Builder")
A licensed general contractor or specialty trade contractor who is assigned to the project through VibeHouse. They interact with the platform through the Trello board, receive daily task assignments, submit progress updates, and participate in the dispute resolution process.

4.3 Tertiary Persona: The Inspector / Compliance Officer
Municipal building inspectors, bank inspectors, or third-party quality assurance professionals who need structured access to build documentation, inspection schedules, and compliance records. They interact through read-only dashboards and inspection scheduling interfaces.

5. System Architecture Overview

5.1 High-Level Architecture
VibeHouse follows a microservices-oriented architecture with an event-driven backbone. The system is decomposed into six primary service domains, each responsible for a distinct capability, communicating through an asynchronous message bus with synchronous API gateways for client-facing operations.

