10.2 Report Delivery
	•	Email: Full HTML report with embedded charts delivered to all stakeholders.
	•	SMS: A condensed 3-line summary with a link to the full report.
	•	Push Notification: Mobile app notification with key metrics and any action items.
	•	Trello Card: A daily report card is created in a dedicated "Reports" list on the Build Board with the full report attached as a PDF.

10.3 Real-Time Notification Engine
Beyond daily reports, the platform sends real-time notifications for critical events including: task completion confirmations, inspection pass/fail results, budget threshold breaches (75%, 90%, 100% of category budgets), schedule slip alerts when the critical path shifts, dispute filings and resolution updates, weather alerts that may impact scheduled work, contractor no-show detection (GPS + Trello activity), and change order requests.

11. Dispute Resolution Engine

11.1 Dispute Detection
The Dispute Engine uses natural language processing to analyze all communications across the platform and proactively identify potential conflicts before they escalate. Detection signals include:

	•	Sentiment Analysis: Negative sentiment trends in Trello comments, emails, or in-app messages. A sustained negative sentiment score triggers a pre-dispute alert.
	•	Schedule Conflict Detection: When two contractors are scheduled for overlapping work areas, when a task is blocked for more than 48 hours, or when a contractor misses two consecutive daily check-ins.
	•	Budget Variance Alerts: When actual costs for a line item exceed the estimate by more than 15%, or when cumulative spending trends indicate a likely budget overrun.
	•	Quality Concern Flags: When inspection checklists have more than 2 failed items, when a contractor requests rework, or when the homeowner flags a concern in any communication.

11.2 Dispute Workflow
When a dispute is identified (either proactively by the AI or manually by a stakeholder), it enters a structured four-stage resolution workflow:

Stage
Duration
Actions
Escalation Trigger
1. Identification
0-4 hours
AI drafts dispute summary, notifies parties, creates Trello card in Dispute list, gathers evidence
Auto-escalates if no acknowledgment in 4 hours
2. Direct Resolution
24-72 hours
Parties negotiate via structured in-app messaging. AI suggests resolutions based on contract terms and precedent
Escalates if no agreement in 72 hours
3. AI Mediation
48-96 hours
AI presents binding resolution options based on contract analysis, cost-benefit analysis, and project impact
Escalates if both parties reject all AI options
4. External Mediation
5-15 days
Platform connects parties with a licensed construction mediator. Full documentation package auto-generated
Legal referral if mediation fails

11.3 Dispute Prompting System
The user-facing dispute interface is conversational. When a dispute is detected or filed, the system prompts the homeowner through a guided process:

	•	"We noticed [specific issue]. Would you like to flag this as a concern?"
	•	"The contractor has responded with [summary]. Here are your options: Accept, Counter-Propose, Escalate."
	•	"Based on your contract and similar projects, we recommend [specific resolution]. Here is our reasoning."
	•	"This dispute has been open for [X days]. Would you like to escalate to formal mediation?"
Every prompt includes full context, relevant contract clauses, cost implications, and schedule impact of each option.

