18. User Interface & UX Flows

18.1 Platform Structure
VibeHouse provides three interfaces: a web application (React/Next.js), a mobile application (React Native), and the Trello Build Board. The web and mobile apps provide the full experience for homeowners. Contractors primarily interact through Trello and a lightweight mobile companion app.

18.2 Core User Flows

Flow 1: Vibe-to-Design (Homeowner)
	9	Onboarding: User creates account, provides build location and rough budget range.
	10	Vibe Session: Guided conversational interface captures the user's vision through natural language and reference image uploads.
	11	AI Processing: System generates Requirement Specification Object and produces 3 floor plan options.
	12	Design Review: User reviews plans in an interactive viewer with AI-annotated explanations of design decisions.
	13	Refinement Loop: User provides feedback ("make the kitchen bigger," "add a mudroom"). AI regenerates.
	14	Plan Finalization: User approves final design. Full construction document set is generated.
	15	Board Creation: Trello Build Board is auto-generated with the complete construction schedule.

Flow 2: Build Monitoring (Homeowner)
	16	Dashboard: User opens the VibeHouse dashboard showing project health, budget, timeline, and today's activities.
	17	Board Check: User navigates to the Trello Build Board (embedded or linked) to see current task status.
	18	Report Review: User reads the daily report delivered to email and available in-app.
	19	Action Response: User responds to any pending decisions, approvals, or dispute prompts.
	20	Photo Review: User browses site photos uploaded by contractors.

Flow 3: Dispute Resolution (Homeowner or Contractor)
	21	Alert: System detects an issue or a stakeholder files a dispute.
	22	Context Gathering: AI presents the dispute summary with full context, contract references, and options.
	23	Response: User selects from resolution options or provides a counter-proposal.
	24	Negotiation: Structured back-and-forth through the platform with AI facilitation.
	25	Resolution: Agreement is reached, documented, and reflected on the Trello board and project schedule.

