22. Appendices

Appendix A: Glossary

Term
Definition
Vibe Code
The process of describing a desired outcome in natural language and having AI translate it into technical specifications and executable plans.
Build Board
The Trello-based project management board that serves as the single source of truth for a construction project.
RSO (Requirement Specification Object)
A structured JSON representation of all design requirements extracted from the user's vibe description.
Critical Path
The longest sequence of dependent tasks that determines the minimum project duration.
Change Order
A formal modification to the original scope, budget, or timeline of the construction project.
RFQ (Request for Quotation)
A formal document sent to contractors requesting a price quote for specific work.
MEP
Mechanical, Electrical, and Plumbing - the three major building systems beyond structural.
DXA
Device Independent Pixels - the unit of measurement used in OOXML documents (1440 DXA = 1 inch).

