Appendix C: Technology Decision Records

TDR-001: Python as Backend Language
Decision: Use Python as the primary backend language for all VibeHouse services.
Rationale: Python provides the strongest ecosystem for AI/ML integration (PyTorch, TensorFlow, scikit-learn, LangChain), mature async frameworks (FastAPI, Celery), excellent data processing libraries (Pandas, NumPy), and the largest pool of available engineering talent. The async capabilities of modern Python (3.12+) with FastAPI achieve performance characteristics competitive with Node.js and Go for I/O-bound workloads, which constitute the majority of VibeHouse operations.
Trade-offs: CPU-bound operations (document rendering, model inference) are offloaded to optimized C/Rust extensions or dedicated worker processes. Critical hot paths may be reimplemented in Rust via PyO3 if profiling indicates need.

TDR-002: Trello as Build Board Platform
Decision: Use Trello via the Atlassian API as the primary Build Board platform rather than building a custom board.
Rationale: Trello provides a familiar UX that reduces onboarding friction, a mature API with webhooks and Power-Ups, mobile apps for contractor access, and Atlassian-grade reliability. Building a custom board would add 3-4 months to Phase 1 with no immediate user benefit.
Trade-offs: Trello API rate limits (300 requests per 10 seconds per token) require careful request management. Custom board migration planned for Phase 3 if Trello becomes a scaling bottleneck.

